Reasoning: The paper focuses on analyzing the dynamics of Meetup groups and events related to software development, which involves social interactions and collaborations among developers. This falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the diversity of Meetup groups, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) in terms of identifying emerging topics and associations among them. Finally, the paper's emphasis on offline social engagements and the categorization of events can be related to social informatics (cs.SI).
